3. What Prior Art 1 actually teaches

US 10,459,887 B1 is mainly about predictive application pre-launch. It determines that an icon satisfies pre-launch criteria when the icon is within a specified display region, such as near the center of the watch display, or has a sufficient size/zoom level. The app can then be loaded into memory before the user selects it. 

The reference also teaches that, after pre-launch, control of drawing an icon may be transferred from the system to the app based on icon size/location. The app may then draw a contextualized or decorated icon, for example showing a calendar appointment or unread email information. Larger icon sizes can lead to more information being drawn on the icon. 

Figure 6 of Prior Art 1 is particularly relevant because it shows entering a “5-up view,” presenting icons, determining whether icons satisfy pre-launch criteria, allowing the app or system to provide contextualized icons, panning within the 5-up view, and allowing applications to decorate additional icons with contextual information. 

